\begin{minipage}{10.5cm}

\textsf{The physics governing the plasma generation in
the polar cap region is a major remaining piece 
of the pulsar puzzle that is not completely solved.
In our studies, we adopt the general approach
of Ruderman \& Sutherland (1975), where sparks 
form in regions of local maxima of the electrical potential.
The electric field between the sparks is influenced by 
the charge deficiency in the spark-forming regions.}
\vspace{0.3cm}

\textsf{In Szary \& van Leeuwen (2017) we introduecd the Modified 
Carousel (MC) model which assumes that electric 
field between sparks is not fully screened which 
leads to plasma circulation
around the global potential extremum at the polar cap 
(see Fig. 2).}

\end{minipage}
